What you need to know:  In the run-up to the August 9, 2022, General Election, Kenya’s power elite stridently weaponised taxes in the presidential contest.After the elections, the country witnessed round two of the tax wars. Framing both rounds one and two of the tax wars is the ‘hustler versus dynasty’ narrative.This third article in the post-truth politics and democracy in Kenya series delves into the second round of Kenya’s tax wars, which has pushed post-truth politics to a fever pitch. It has also increased the risk of stability.